cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing a discourse segmenter using machine learning techniques. The paper focuses on natural language processing and specifically on discourse segmentation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
